# Bina — Full Project Context

## What it is

Bina is a **100% local** AI semantic file manager for macOS. Point it at a folder,
it indexes every `.pdf/.docx/.txt/.md` using a local LLM (llama3.2:3b via Ollama)
to extract summary/keywords/entities/doc_type, embeds each file with nomic-embed-text
(768-dim), stores vectors in ChromaDB, and builds a NetworkX knowledge graph where
edges = cosine similarity ≥ 0.72. You search in plain English; the query is embedded,
matched against vectors, expanded through the graph, and shown as an Obsidian-style
interactive graph. **Nothing leaves the machine.**

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| Desktop shell | Electron (CommonJS — NOT `"type":"module"`) |
| Frontend | React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind |
| State management | Zustand (`src/store/appStore.ts`) |
| Graph rendering | D3 v7 force simulation + HTML Canvas (manual pan/zoom, no d3-zoom) |
| Backend | FastAPI sidecar on port 8765, spawned by Electron |
| AI | Ollama: `llama3.2:3b` (LLM) + `nomic-embed-text` (embed) |
| Vector store | ChromaDB at `~/.bina/chroma/` |
| Relational DB | SQLite at `~/.bina/bina.db` via SQLAlchemy |
| Graph | NetworkX in-memory, per-workspace, Louvain community detection |
| File watching | watchdog FSEvents |
| IPC | Electron contextBridge (`window.bina.api.*`) |

